    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "The core decision logic. Calculates a 0–100 score from five weighted factors: repayment history (40 pts, weighted heaviest since past behavior is the strongest predictor), debt-to-income ratio (25 pts), employment stability (15 pts), loan-to-income reasonableness (10 pts), dependents (10 pts). Outputs a risk category (low/medium/high) plus the full breakdown for transparency. Rule-based and deterministic on purpose — for a financial decision, every score must be explainable and reproducible, which a pure LLM judgment can't reliably guarantee."
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -720,
        400
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "6666b455-e688-47dd-b556-f20c7cf4ef22",
      "name": "Sticky Note4"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Sends the score and breakdown to an LLM, asking it to translate the numbers into a plain-English explanation and recommendation. The LLM never decides the score itself — it only explains a decision that's already been made, which keeps the actual risk assessment consistent and auditable."
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
